State of North Carolina
v.
Omeako Lavon Brisbon No. 38P06-2 Supreme Court of North Carolina. January 26, 2017 Daniel P. O'Brien, Special Deputy Attorney General, Derrick Mertz, Assistant Attorney General, William R. West, District Attorney, For State of NC. Bruce T. Cunningham, Jr., Attorney at Law, Southern Pines, For Brisbon, Omeako Levon.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 5th of December 2016 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Cumberland County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 26th of January 2017."
